\section{Results}
On the basis of a detailed analysis of all of the isolated molecules and by comparison of their ${ }^{1} \mathrm{H}$ NMR and ${ }^{13} \mathrm{C}$ NMR spectral data and $[\alpha]_{D}$ values with those reported in the literature, $4-7$ and 10 were readily identified as a lobane-type diterpenoid, loba-8,10,13(15)-triene-17,18-diol (4) [10], lobatetraene (5) [10], fuscol (6) [9,10], 7, an unnamed prenyleudesmane diterpene [11], and sarcophytol B (10) [12], respectively.

Sinupol (8) was obtained as a colorless oil. Its molecular formula was established as $\mathrm{C}_{20} \mathrm{H}_{32} \mathrm{O}$ by (+)-HR-EIMS, indicating five degrees of unsaturation in the molecule. The ${ }^{13} \mathrm{C}$ NMR and HSQC spectra of 8 exhibited the presence of 20 carbon resonances, including five methyl groups, five sp ${ }^{3}$ methylene, two $\mathrm{sp}^{3}$ methine, two $\mathrm{sp}^{3}$ quaternary, four $\mathrm{sp}^{2}$ methine, and two $\mathrm{sp}^{2}$ quaternary carbons. A detailed comparison of the NMR data of 8 with those of 7 suggested that 8 is a 1-dehydroxyl product of 7 for the identical chemical shifts in the side chains and significant carbon signal differences $\left(\delta_{\mathrm{C}-1} 76.9, \delta_{\mathrm{C}-2}\right.$ 33.0, and $\delta_{\mathrm{C}-10} 38.5$ for $7, \delta_{\mathrm{C}-1} 38.1, \delta_{\mathrm{C}-2} 23.2$, and $\delta_{\mathrm{C}-10} 32.4$ for 8 ) around $\mathrm{C}-1$. To fully elucidate the structure of 8 , its two-dimensional (2D) NMR spectra were extensively analyzed. The ${ }^{1} \mathrm{H}$ and ${ }^{13} \mathrm{C}$ NMR resonances revealed the presences of one disubstituted and two trisubstituted double bonds, including a conjugated diene fragment (Figure 2). Since the three double bonds accounted for three degrees of unsaturation, the remaining two degrees of unsaturation were attributed to a bicyclic ring system in 8 . Further analysis of the ${ }^{1} \mathrm{H}-{ }^{1} \mathrm{H}$ COSY spectrum revealed the presence of three coupling systems $(\mathbf{a}-\mathbf{c})$ from $\mathrm{H}_{2}-1$ to $\mathrm{H}-3, \mathrm{H}-5$ to $\mathrm{H}_{2}-9$, and $\mathrm{H}-12$ to $\mathrm{H}-14$ (Figure 2).The key $\mathrm{HMBC}$ correlations from $\mathrm{H}_{3}-16$ to C-3/C-4/C-5, from $\mathrm{H}_{3}-17$ to C-1/C-5/C-10/C-9, and from $\mathrm{H}_{2}-6$ to C-4/C-5/C-10/C-11 confirmed the presence of the bicyclic ring moiety. The side chain was connected to $\mathrm{C}-7$ of the decalin ring moiety through C-11, and was supported by crosspeaks from $\mathrm{H}_{3}-18$ to C-7/C-11/C-12 and from $\mathrm{H}_{3}-19 / \mathrm{H}_{3}-20$ to C-14/C-15 in the HMBC spectrum. Thus, the planar structure of 8 was confirmed (Figure 2).

