\subsection{Determination of the Absolute Configurations of Compounds 8 and 9 by TDDFT ECD Calculations}
Conformational searches were carried out using the torsional sampling (MCMM) method and OPLS\_2005 force field. Conformers above 1\% population were re-optimized at the B3LYP/6-311G (d, p) level with IEFPCM (Polarizable Continuum Model using the Integral Equation Formalism variant) solvent model for acetonitrile [15]. For the resulting geometries, ECD spectra were obtained by TDDFT calculations performed with the same functional basis set and solvent model as the energy optimization. Finally, the Boltzmann-averaged ECD spectra of the two compounds were obtained with SpecDis1.62 [20].

\subsection{Bioactivity Assay}
Recombinant PTP1B catalytic domain was expressed and purified according to a previous report [16]. The enzymatic activities of the PTP1B catalytic domain were determined at $30{ }^{\circ} \mathrm{C}$ by monitoring the hydrolysis of $p \mathrm{NPP}$. The dephosphorylation of $p \mathrm{NPP}$ generated product $p \mathrm{NP}$, which was monitored at an absorbance of $405 \mathrm{~nm}$ by the EnVision multi label plate reader (Perkin Elmer Life Sciences, Boston, MA). In an atypical $100 \mu \mathrm{L}$ assay mixture containing $50 \mathrm{mmol} / \mathrm{L} \mathrm{3}$-[ $\mathrm{N}$-morpholino] propanesulfonic acid (MOPs), $\mathrm{pH}$ 6.5, $2 \mathrm{mmol} / \mathrm{L} p \mathrm{NPP}$, and $30 \mathrm{nmol} / \mathrm{L}$ recombinant PTP1B, activities were continuously monitored and the initial rate of hydrolysis was determined using the early linear region of the enzymatic reaction kinetic curve. The $\mathrm{IC}_{50}$ was calculated with Prism 4 software (Graphpad, San Diego, CA). Compounds 5-10 were tested in vitro and compounds 5, 6, and 10 were inactive. Interestingly, $7-9$ exhibited moderate inhibitory activity against PTP1B with $\mathrm{IC}_{50}$ values $72.4 \mu \mathrm{M}, 63.9 \mu \mathrm{M}$, and $51.8 \mu \mathrm{M}$, respectively, with the positive control of oleanolic acid ( $\left.\mathrm{IC}_{50}=2.56 \mu \mathrm{M}\right)$.

